cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about a library for structured prediction in natural language processing (NLP) that is designed to integrate with deep learning frameworks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of auto-differentiation and vectorized operations, which are common in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the library can be used for tasks such as segmentation and alignment, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
